cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.GT 

The paper presents a vision-only model for gaming AI using a deep convolutional network architecture trained in a purely supervised imitation learning context. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the model, which suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves game theory and simulations, which could place it in the game theory (cs.GT) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
